                    <h1 data-uuid="6dfc91fb6a9d47779f7737fe8d83facc">Adjusting to Peace</h1>
                    <div class="yellow-star-yellow-bar" data-uuid="465be1d278d74011851c6035b7755456"></div>
                    <h2 data-uuid="947cbd9632744a95993a12d25450cd99">The Big Idea</h2>
                    <p data-uuid="d4794d142baf4e98bbd25e3d4a11384f">After World War II, Americans adjusted to new
                        challenges both at home and around the world.</p>
                </div>
            </article>
            <article data-uuid="bfa2591203a44909ba689f8f9c491599">
                <h3 class="if-you-were-there" data-uuid="25e73da8eb0b4ac48da3f40e42dcbcd5">If YOU were there...</h3>
                <p data-uuid="6065020cda6b407aa4d41226e2176b25">You are an adviser to President Harry S. Truman in July
                    1945. You have traveled with him to Potsdam, outside the ruined city of Berlin,
                    where Allied leaders are discussing postwar plans. Everyone agrees that steps
                    must be taken to prevent another world war. But you are worried that Soviet
                    leader Joseph Stalin cannot be trusted.</p>
            </article>
